        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 2:56PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 256 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near McNeil to near Emerson. Movement was
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Norphlet, Calion, Newell, Mount Holly, Laughlin, McNeil, El Dorado,
College Hill, Atlanta, Wesson, Kenova, Spotville, Medlock,
Catesville, Hew Hope, Ebenezer, Calhoun, Village, Lisbon, and
Aurelle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for northwestern
Louisiana.</instruction>
